        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T18:41:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I left the parsing of this new boolean value done in the same way as we parse the boolean `inherited`.\n\nI think you have a point though, that\u0027s not what we want.\nWe should raise an `IOException` instead, so that it will be wrapped in a `InvalidOwnersFileException` surfacing the misconfiguration.\n\nWe should also change the parsing of `inherited`, add a unit test for this and change the signature of `toMatcher` to bubble up the exception.\n\nHow do you feel if we make this a follow-up to avoid bloating this change even further?",
      "parentUuid": "c56987d4_accbf2bf",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 48,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 48,
