        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T18:41:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, the overall default is `true`.\n\nBut here we are parsing one specific `OWNERS`, and we must understand if the field is set or not.\n\n- `true` means explicitly enabled\n- `false` means explicitly disabled\n- `null` means not set\n\nIf we defaulted to true during parsing, every missing field would look like an explicit `true`, and inheritance would stop working correctly.\n\nIf after, applying inheritance, the value is still `null`, then we default to `true` in the follow-up change [here](https://gerrit.googlesource.com/plugins/owners/+/refs/changes/04/558304/5/owners-common/src/main/java/com/googlesource/gerrit/owners/common/PathOwners.java#268)",
      "parentUuid": "fb0badd0_8194b8d8",
